  <section class="mb-5">
    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">3. Typische Einführungs-Phasen</h2>
    <ol class="small">
      <li><strong>Scope & Datenquellen Auswahl</strong>: Priorisierte Quellsysteme & Compliance Treiber definieren.</li>
      <li><strong>Foundational Setup</strong>: Data Map aktivieren, Integration Runtime deployen, Service Principals & RBAC.</li>
      <li><strong>Scanning & Klassifizierung</strong>: Erste vollständige Scans, Klassifizierungs-Tuning (False Positives minimieren).</li>
      <li><strong>Catalog Curation</strong>: Glossary Terms, Steward-Rollen, Tagging, Data Ownership etablieren.</li>
      <li><strong>Lineage & Quality Integration</strong>: Pipeline-Quellen anbinden (ADF/Synapse), Data Quality Signals verknüpfen.</li>
      <li><strong>Policy & Access Governance</strong>: Testen zentraler Data Policies & Sensitivity Label Enforcement.</li>
      <li><strong>Rollout & Enablement</strong>: Schulungen, Self-Service Guidelines, KPI Tracking (Adoption, Query Success).</li>
    </ol>
  </section>
